comments:
In 1889 the part of the parish of Abergele in Rhyl Urban District 
    became part of Flintshire. In 1894 this area became a separate unnamed parish and the remaining part of Abergele was abolished and divided between the parishes 
    of Abergele Urban and Abergele Rural.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Abergele. See 
    also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Abergele in Abergele 
    & Pensarn Urban District. See also Table 2, note (a).
See Table 2, note (a).

    2, note (d).
See Table 2, note (d).

    Table 2, note (a).

Created 1.10.1895 from the Denbighshire part of the parish of 
    St. Asaph. See also Table 2, note (a).
